As of midnight yesterday, there were 367 new cases of coronavirus infection, 93 more cases than at 4 p.m. yesterday, bringing the total number of confirmed cases to 7,134, the death rate to 50 and the cure rate to 130.

So far, in addition to confirmed cases, the cumulative number of people tested for the virus in South Korea is 181384,24 hours 9,962 new people, 162008 test results were negative, the remaining 19,376 results are not yet available.

Source: Korea Central Epidemic Prevention Countermeasures Department

Of the 7,134 cases confirmed as of midnight, 5,378 were in Taegu and 1,081 were in North Gyeongsang Province, accounting for 75.4% and 15.2% respectively. Gyeonggi Province and Seoul have also confirmed 142 and 120 cases, respectively.

Although the number of new cases confirmed in a single day has been slowly declining, the current situation in South Korea is still very serious. Of the 6,767 cases diagnosed as of midnight on July 7,72.8% were associated with group infection. A total of 4,297 cases, or 63.5 per cent, were confirmed with Xintiandi church-related cases, with the majority coming from Taegu (3,716 cases) and Qingbei (466 cases) .

At present, in all parts of South Korea, especially in Daegu and the surrounding areas, where the epidemic is most serious, there are still clusters of infections and cases of community spread, and the health sector remains on high alert.

The South Korean government closed an apartment building in Daegu for the first time Monday after 46 people were confirmed. It is understood that the apartment building is a municipal rental apartments, mainly for unmarried women under 35 years of age, a total of 137 households, 142 residents. Health Department investigation found that 94 of the apartment residents are Xintiandi believers.

The same day, Korean Air also appeared a second confirmed infection of the new coronavirus crew. The 36-year-old flight attendant was on a Los angeles-to-incheon flight late last month, Korean Air and local authorities said Tuesday.

Korean Air's first confirmed infection on the 20th of last month in this trip from Los Angeles to Incheon on the flight KE012 duty, the crew was confirmed on the 25th of last month. Korean Air said other flight attendants on the same flight tested negative for the virus, and the company plans to extend the isolation of 30 other flight attendants as a precaution.

According to the South Korean Foreign Ministry, as of 2:00 pm that day, the number of countries and regions that have taken immigration control measures against South Korea due to the new pneumonia outbreak has increased to 103. The South Korean government is considering arranging charter flights next week to evacuate expatriates from Iran, which would be the first time South Korea has evacuated expatriates from a specific country, not just from a specific region abroad.

It is understood that the current stay in Iran of 220 South Korean citizens, about 100 people are expected to return by charter flight. They will be tested for the virus at designated facilities upon their return and will be quarantined for 14 days.

As the new crown pneumonia epidemic continues to spread in the country, the Korean catering and film industry has been a major impact. According to Yonhap, the restaurant industry has borne the brunt, with a nearly 60 percent drop in customers, while the film industry has seen its lowest attendance in 16 years, with more than 50 titles yet to be set for release.

A 59.2 percent drop in diners was the result of a door-to-door and telephone survey of 600 restaurants conducted Feb. 25-28 by the Ministry of Agriculture, forestry, animal husbandry and food, the Korean Food and Beverage Industry Research Institute, a branch of the Central Committee of the Korean catering industry, said Wednesday. The drop in customers was 26.5 percentage points more than the previous week (32.7%) .

95.2% of the restaurants surveyed reported a gradual decline in customers since the first confirmed case in the country on January 20. By region, North Gyeongsang Province and South Gyeongsang Province, which have more confirmed cases, saw the biggest drop, at 66.8 per cent. Then came Gangwon Province (65.9%) , South Chungcheong Province and North Chungcheong Province (65.2%) . By type of restaurant, Korean restaurants saw the biggest drop, at 64.1 per cent. Japanese, western and fried chicken restaurants each accounted for 55.2 per cent.

South Korean film distributors have delayed the release of new films as the outbreak has spread rapidly around the cities of Daegu and North Gyeongsang Province, causing public unrest and leading to a flight to safety.

According to figures released by the Korean Film Council (Kofic) on Thursday, only 59,895 people watched the movie the previous day, the lowest number in 16 years.

More than 50 films originally scheduled for release in March and April have yet to set a release date, as it is difficult to predict when the new pneumonia outbreak will be brought under control, according to major film distributors, some publishers are also considering postponing the release date to the second half or the first half of next year.

However, given that attendance did not return to normal until two months after the Middle East Respiratory Syndrome (MERS) outbreak subsided in 2015, it is expected to take a while for the box office to return to pre-outbreak levels once the outbreak is contained.

In addition, the new film also made mistakes. The production company is monitoring the situation and postponing shooting if a crew member is confirmed to have a new coronavirus infection during filming, the company said. In this case, part of the view that the first half of next year, the Korean film May Appear Blank period.
